      "solution": "n = int(input())\na = [int(x) for x in input().split()] + [999]\n\nfor i in range(n):\n  if a[i] < a[i + 1]:\n    print(i)\n    exit()\n",
      "statement": "Given a sequence of [[N]] positive integers, find the minimum number of operations required to transform it into a strictly increasing sequence. The only allowed operation is to multiply any element by -1.\n\nA sequence a_1, ⋯, a_N is strictly increasing if a_i < a_{i+1} for all 1 ≤ i < N.\n\n<<Example:>>\n\nConsider the sequence 7, 3, 2, 6, 8.\n\n1. Multiply the first element 7 by -1. The sequence becomes -7, 3, 2, 6, 8.\n2. Multiply the second element 3 by -1. The sequence becomes -7, -3, 2, 6, 8, which is strictly increasing.\n\nIn this example, the minimum number of operations required is 2.",
